TI  - Nash equilibrium seeking of general linear multi-agent systems in the cooperation-competition network
T2  - SYSTEMS & CONTROL LETTERS
AB  - In this paper, a novel Nash equilibrium (NE) seeking problem for linear multi-agent system (MAS) is constructed in the cooperation-competition network (C-C network). There are two relationships between agents: cooperation and competition, and the objective of each agent is to optimize the total cost function of all cooperators. Different from the existing multi-coalition game problem, each agent only knows if he is in a cooperative or competitive relationship with his neighbors, therefore he is unaware of which coalition he belongs to. To solve this problem, the game algorithm is proposed based on asymmetric local information interaction, that is, different auxiliary variables that interact with neighbors with different relationships to estimate the total cost function of all cooperators, state feedback and gradient descent are used to stabilize the system and solve the optimal solution. The convergence of the algorithm is analyzed by Lyapunov stability theory. Numerical simulation finally verifies the effectiveness of the proposed algorithms.(c) 2023 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.
